Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the 2019 Government Affairs Conference of the Credit Union National Association. He thanked credit unions for their role in helping Americans achieve the American Dream and highlighted the work of individuals in the industry. Pence also praised President Donald Trump for his support of credit unions and his efforts to roll back regulations, promote economic growth, and secure the country's southern border. He urged credit union leaders to advocate for border security and to oppose socialism. Pence encouraged them to continue serving their communities and investing in the American Dream.